 its binding free energy. As well,\nseveral mutants were more susceptible to loss of metals and monomerization than\nthe disulfide-reduced or apo forms of SOD1. Distance constraints are required\nto calculate free energies for metal binding and dimer separation, which are\nvalidated using thermodynamic cycles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Nov 2012 19:12:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-02-20"}
