s Swift UV photometry shows that symbiotic stars with harder X-ray\nemission tend to have stronger UV flickering, which is usually associated with\naccretion through a disk. To place these new observations in the context of\nprevious work on X-ray emission from symbiotic star.............\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Nov 2012 20:32:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Nov 2013 14:32:34 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 5 Nov 2013 16:03:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-11-06"}
